<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-478-390  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 478 390.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  May 30 1990 n1435* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM ships 3390-3 Fast Write, Dual Copy features this week. (IBMCorp to offer Dual Copy and Fast Write features in 3390-3 diskcontroller)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Peripheral ControllersHard DiskEnhancements.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM SHIPS 3390-3 FAST WRITE, DUAL COPY FEATURES THIS WEEKandM;IBM has (just) met its November 14 promise that the Fast Write and Dual Copyfeatures for the 3990-3 disk controller would be available in May, and thetwo Extended Functions are being made available via a no-charge specify codeon the 3990 Model 3.andP;  Also, 3990 Extended Function Dual Copy for 3380 disks,available since the first quarter of 1990 through an orderable engineeringchange, can now be ordered via a no-charge specify code on the 3990-3.andP;  Whenthe controller is fitted with the new functions, it won't support 3380 ModelA04, AA4 and B04 drives.andP;  The feature can be ordered on new 3990-3s and as afield upgrade for existing ones - in the latter case it has to be shut downfor microcode reload.andO;</TEXT></DOC>